b9=A.iX("Important for Mains GS-II (International Relations) and GS-III (Economy). FTA impact on domestic industries, agricultural concerns, and ISDS mechanism are key discussion points.","",c3,"","After over a decade of negotiations, India and the European Union have finalized a landmark Comprehensive Free Trade Agreement (FTA) that promises to reshape bilateral economic relations.\n\nScope and Coverage:\nThe agreement covers trade in goods, services, investment protection, intellectual property rights, government procurement, and dispute resolution mechanisms. It is one of the most comprehensive FTAs India has signed.\n\nKey Highlights:\n\u2022 Tariff Elimination: Phased reduction of tariffs on over 90% of traded goods over 7-10 years\n\u2022 Services: Enhanced market access for Indian IT, pharmaceutical, and professional services in EU markets\n\u2022 Investment: Bilateral investment protection with an investor-state dispute settlement (ISDS) mechanism\n\u2022 Digital Trade: New chapter on e-commerce and digital trade facilitation\n\u2022 Sustainability: Binding commitments on climate action, labor standards, and environmental protection\n\nEconomic Impact:\nThe FTA is projected to increase bilateral trade by 30% within five years, from the current ~\u20ac120 billion. India's textile, pharmaceutical, automotive, and IT sectors are expected to benefit significantly, while EU firms gain improved access to India's growing consumer market of 1.4 billion people.\n\nIndia-EU bilateral trade currently makes the EU India's third-largest trading partner after the USA and China.","","Mains",A.a(["Negotiations initiated (2007)","Stalled and resumed multiple times","Key areas finalized: goods, services, IP","Sustainability chapter added","ISDS mechanism agreed","FTA signed and ratification process begins","Phased tariff reduction (7-10 years)"],b8),"","a4","https://picsum.photos/seed/india_eu_trade/800/400",!0,p,B.bZ,"EU-FTA: E=Elimination of tariffs (90%), U=Upgraded services access, F=Full IP protection, T=Trade increase 30%, A=Agreement on sustainability",a6,B.ag,q,o,b9,"","India and the European Union conclude a comprehensive Free Trade Agreement covering goods, services, investments, intellectual property, and sustainability commitments.","","India-EU Free Trade Agreement: A New Era of Economic Partnership",a3)
