q=A.iX("Important for GS-II (Polity) and GS-I (Women issues). Focus on constitutional journey, delimitation linkage, and comparison with local body reservations already at 33-50%.","",p,"","In a historic session, the Indian Parliament unanimously passed the Constitution (One Hundred and Twenty-Eighth Amendment) Bill, officially named the Nari Shakti Vandan Adhiniyam, providing 33% reservation for women in the Lok Sabha and state legislative assemblies.\n\nKey Provisions:\n\u2022 One-third of all seats in the Lok Sabha and state legislative assemblies will be reserved for women\n\u2022 Sub-reservation within the women's quota for Scheduled Castes (SC) and Scheduled Tribes (ST)\n\u2022 The reservation will rotate among different constituencies after each delimitation\n\u2022 The reservation will be effective for 15 years from the date of commencement\n\u2022 Parliament may extend it beyond 15 years by law\n\nImplementation Timeline:\nThe reservation will come into effect only after the next Census is conducted and a fresh delimitation exercise is completed based on that Census data.\n\nConstitutional Journey:\n- The Women's Reservation Bill was first introduced in the 12th Lok Sabha in 1996\n- It was passed by the Rajya Sabha in 2010 but lapsed in the Lok Sabha\n- The 128th Amendment was introduced and passed in a special session of Parliament\n- It amends Articles 239AA, 330, 332, and 334, and inserts new Articles 330A and 332A\n\nSignificance:\nCurrently, women constitute only about 15% of the Lok Sabha. The reservation aims to address the severe underrepresentation of women in India's legislative bodies.","",b,A.a(["Bill introduced in 12th Lok Sabha (1996)","Rajya Sabha passed (2010) but lapsed in LS","128th Amendment introduced in special session","Passed unanimously by both Houses","Census to be conducted","Delimitation exercise based on Census","Reservation takes effect"],b8),"","a6","https://picsum.photos/seed/parliament_india/800/400",!0,n,B.bZ,"NARI: N=Nari Shakti, A=Amendment 128th, R=Reservation 33%, I=Implementation after Census",a0,B.ag,o,m,q,"","Parliament passes the 128th Constitutional Amendment providing 33% reservation for women in Lok Sabha and state assemblies \u2014 a historic step after three decades of demand.","","Nari Shakti Vandan Adhiniyam: 33% Women's Reservation Bill Passed",a3)
